{"sectionId":760,"sectionIdLiteral":"760","humanId":"lesson-337","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"My sinlessness protects me from all harm.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 337"},"annotation":"W-337","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-337\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"760#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"760#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>My sinlessness ensures me perfect peace, eternal safety, everlasting love, freedom forever from all thought of loss; complete deliverance from suffering.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"760#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>And only happiness can be my state, for only happiness is given me.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"760#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>What must I do to know all this is mine?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"760#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>I must accept Atonement for myself, and nothing more.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"760#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>God has already done all things that need be done.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"760#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>And I must learn I need do nothing of myself, for I need but accept my Self, my sinlessness, created for me, now already mine, to feel God‚Äôs Love protecting me from harm, to understand my Father loves His Son; to know I am the Son my Father loves.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"760#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"760#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>You Who created me in sinlessness are not mistaken about what I am.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"760#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>I was mistaken when I thought I sinned, but I accept Atonement for myself.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"760#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Father, my dream is ended now.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"760#2:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>Amen.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"My sinle